body:
OSX is a mess :-) Or, at least, my instance of python on it is.

```
$ python2.7 sync.py -i tripit.json
Input file is tripit.json
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "sync.py", line 81, in <module>
    main(sys.argv[1:])
  File "sync.py", line 27, in main
    for f in flightdiary.get_flights():
  File "Downloads/tripit-to-flightdiary-master/flightdiary.py", line 42, in get_flights
    from_=bs4.BeautifulSoup(row[2], "html5lib").text,
  File "/Library/Python/2.7/site-packages/bs4/__init__.py", line 165, in __init__
    % ",".join(features))
bs4.FeatureNotFound: Couldn't find a tree builder with the features you requested: html5lib. Do you need to install a parser library?
$ sudo -H pip2.7 install html5lib
Requirement already satisfied: html5lib in /Library/Python/2.7/site-packages
Requirement already satisfied: six in /System/Library/Frameworks/Python.framework/Versions/2.7/Extras/lib/python (from html5lib)
Requirement already satisfied: webencodings in /Library/Python/2.7/site-packages (from html5lib)
Requirement already satisfied: setuptools>=18.5 in /Library/Python/2.7/site-packages (from html5lib)
Requirement already satisfied: packaging>=16.8 in /Library/Python/2.7/site-packages (from setuptools>=18.5->html5lib)
Requirement already satisfied: appdirs>=1.4.0 in /Library/Python/2.7/site-packages (from setuptools>=18.5->html5lib)
Requirement already satisfied: pyparsing in /System/Library/Frameworks/Python.framework/Versions/2.7/Extras/lib/python (from packaging>=16.8->setuptools>=18.5->html5lib)
$
```

So, it's installed but bs4 can't find it.

Workaround was to edit flightdiary.py and change all instances where you imported html5lib to html.parser.

```
$ python sync.py -i tripit.json
Input file is tripit.json
Added flight 2011-09-07 BHX AMS WW1011
Added flight 2011-09-08 AMS BHX WW1014
[...]
```

Yay!
title: OSX:  bs4 won't import html5lib
